            "text": "Explicit Feedback (Ratings)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Explicit feedback is a signal that a human deliberately gives about an agent output: a thumbs up, a star rating, a label, or a comment. Unlike implicit signals (time spent reading, edits made), explicit feedback has unambiguous polarity. Collected well, it forms the ground truth dataset for evaluating, fine-tuning, and monitoring agent quality over time."
          }
        ]
